Scope and Responsibilities of the Committee
The Grievance Redressal Committee shall schedule a date for hearing the complaint and communicate it to the Chairperson and the aggrieved person, either in writing or electronically, as feasible.
The quorum for any meeting shall be three members, including the Chairperson but excluding the special invitee.
The term of the Chairperson and Members shall be two years, while the term of the special invitee shall be one year.
An aggrieved student or person may appear in person or be represented by an authorized individual to present their case.
The Grievance Redressal Committee shall adhere to the principles of natural justice when hearing grievances.
The Committee shall ensure that every application is resolved as quickly as possible, preferably within ten days and not later than one month from the date of receipt.
Upon concluding the proceedings, the Committee shall issue an order—along with reasons—deemed appropriate to redress the grievance and provide suitable relief to the affected party.
The final order shall be communicated to the aggrieved student or person, and the University shall act in compliance with the order.
The aforementioned grievances may be reported to the Chairman of the committee by any means and additionally through the following email address grievance.studentgrievances@vvitu.ac.in
